#NihaoChina! Meet Shangri-La! The Pudacuo national park in NW Yunnan’s Diqing, is presenting its natural beauty at the beginning of winter. legacy.full_text: From 1941 when Chennault was invited to #Yunnan to form the AVG to the recent visit by the Flying Tigers veterans. The healthy and stable development of China-US relations in the new era requires the participation and support of "a new generation of #FlyingTigers". #APEC2023 https://t.co/2aOC9h5CEy

Seeing her father’s traces and stories in the museum, Jane Bonner Scott was deeply touched, and she also wished the #FlyingTigers spirit to be passed down to the future generation. https://t.co/OpG7dtsMcX
When the #FlyingTigers were fighting for China, local people welcomed them and had a wonderful time together. https://t.co/EEuuP81jlQ
Stephen Bonner, a #veteran of the Flying Tigers left uniquely beautiful memories in #Kunming. His daughter Jane Bonner Scott visited #Kunming recently. #FlyingTigers https://t.co/RT6EGM0nHC

Come to #Nujiang to see the magnificent mountains and rivers in NW #Yunnan’s Nujiang prefecture!
The surging river is rushing, roaring to express the magnificent beauty in #Dulongjiang River and the #Gaoligong Mountain. #NaturalBeauty https://t.co/t5fzxkvmMM

Mysterious #earthforest was born by nature in #Yuanmou county, central Yunnan’s #Chuxiong prefecture, where the Yuanmou ancient people were lived 170 million years ago. Under the effect of water erosion, the Yuanmou earth forest is formed into different shapes. #NatureWonders https://t.co/RqlpuLx88w

Known as Zaojuntang, the #candy is a traditional snack among #Yunnan people. It also carries the sweetness of many people's childhood memories. Geng Yanchun, the inheritor of candy-making skills in #Jinning county, Yunnan’s #Kunming, shows the process. #YunnanLifestyle https://t.co/WXdw78SqRW

#Butterflyies and #bees were seen in the pink #flowers. Silk floss trees are blooming recently in NW #Yunnan‘s Lushui city. The city is full of pink #romance. #naturephotography https://t.co/YcRTzi6zyH

#Mile is a city that is well-known for #redwine in central #Yunnan’s #Honghe Prefecture, which is the largest wine producer in #Yunnan. Thanks to the pleasant climate and fertile soil, the #grapes show the characteristics of early maturity and high quality. https://t.co/HilVOdDXJQ
The #DianchiLake today is extremely beautiful with the blue sky and white clouds. The black-headed #seagulls are back to #Kunming for wintering these days. #AmazingChina https://t.co/40AzdSoCY1

Haha, have you ever seen the huge and beautiful #fruit resembling a colorful #pineapple? It’s called Kadsura coccinea which is a delicious and sweet fruit in Jinping County, south Yunnan’s Honghe prefecture.  #ExoticFruit https://t.co/iSF4vDGkeA

The visit to #Yunnan, is inspired by Chinese President Xi Jinping, who replied to a letter from Greene, Moyer and McMullen. He hopes that the spirit of the #FlyingTigers will be carried on from generation to generation between the people of China and the US. https://t.co/3e6yS9GluI

Harry Moyer has just celebrated his 103rd birthday in China, and Melvin McMullen is 98 years old. The #FlyingTigers veterans and their families returned to #Yunnan for the purpose of passing down the spirit of the Flying Tigers and carrying forward the Sino-US folk #friendship. https://t.co/Qc65OwqVOa
A special American delegation visited #Yunnan province from November 2 to 4.  Exhibits at the #Kunming #FlyingTigers Museum brought the Americans back to the eventful days. https://t.co/cjbDstA1mS

The #FlyingTigers, or the #US 14th Air Force in China, have a special historical bond with #Yunnan. Born in the province, the Flying Tigers joined the Chinese people in the worldwide anti-fascist war some 80 years ago, shedding their blood and sacrificing their lives. https://t.co/ihsllbnpJ9
